Lessons learned:

    1. If you get to a point where you cannot use "git log" or "git status" as you get
        a "gitdiff permission denied", be sure you invalidate the git pager:
            git config --global core.pager cat

    2. If you use "ajv-keywords" npm, you might get the annoying message in Jest TDD:
            console.warn
                keywords option as map is deprecated, pass array

           Get rid of it by requiring ajv_keywords below the new Ajv():

        const ajvValidate = new Ajv({
          allErrors: true,
          // eslint-disable-next-line global-require
          // keywords: require('ajv-keywords/dist/definitions'),
          strict: false, // to get rid of console.warning
        })
          .addFormat('email', /^[\w.+]+@\w+\.\w+$/)
          .addSchema([userSchema])
          .compile(userSchema);

        require('ajv-keywords/dist/definitions')(ajvValidate)

    3. If you get: "Jest did not exit one second after the test run has completed"
            then add --detectOpenHandles to your jest command to find what's preventing
            jest to exit. This is a BUG in Nodev15 onwards(???)

            Jest and RANDOMBYTESREQUEST open handles

            Solution: add --forceExit to jest command

    4. In async tests you may get:
            code: 'ERR_UNHANDLED_REJECTION'

            Solution:
             put an "await" in front of the function in the try portion of the test
